It's a pass, Viktor.

1231
01:43:27,826 --> 01:43:30,787
A one-day travel emergency visa
with your name on it.

1232
01:43:30,829 --> 01:43:32,622
- Wha... Visa?
- Yes.

1233
01:43:32,664 --> 01:43:34,875
- From your friend?
- Yeah.

1234
01:43:34,958 --> 01:43:38,920
Just go to New York, find that last name
and put it in the can.

1235
01:43:39,796 --> 01:43:40,881
- I go New York?
- Yes.

1236
01:43:41,006 --> 01:43:42,465
I go New York!

1237
01:43:50,682 --> 01:43:54,144
Amelia, you come with.
You come with me to New York.

1238
01:43:57,272 --> 01:44:01,985
Your friend do this for me?
Why he do this for me?

1239
01:44:04,029 --> 01:44:06,031
He did it for me.

1240
01:44:08,033 --> 01:44:12,120
I told you to stay away from me, Viktor.
But you didn't understand.

1241
01:44:12,204 --> 01:44:16,082
- I think you were confused.
- No, I confused about everything.

1242
01:44:16,166 --> 01:44:18,793
I not confused... Not this. Not this.

1243
01:44:21,004 --> 01:44:24,799
I'm sorry. I'm running late.

1244
01:44:24,883 --> 01:44:27,928
Amelia. Why you go? Why you go?

1245
01:44:29,387 --> 01:44:32,891
You know what Napoleon
gave Josephine as a wedding present?

1246
01:44:32,974 --> 01:44:35,018
It was a gold locket.

1247
01:44:35,101 --> 01:44:38,438
And on the inside,
he made an inscription.

1248
01:44:43,235 --> 01:44:45,320
"Destiny".

1249
01:44:48,073 --> 01:44:50,075
Destiny.

1250
01:44:52,327 --> 01:44:55,580
...rejoice in the streets
as well as in their local taverns.

1251
01:44:55,664 --> 01:45:00,418
The Krakozhian flag waved goodbye
from high atop the parliament buildings.

1252
01:45:00,502 --> 01:45:02,546
It is a clear sign of the power...

1253
01:45:04,714 --> 01:45:07,467
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

1254
01:45:08,260 --> 01:45:09,594
I missed you.

1255
01:45:12,764 --> 01:45:14,724
Come on.

1256
01:45:27,612 --> 01:45:29,114
Next.

1257
01:45:29,865 --> 01:45:31,867
Viktor.

1258
01:45:33,785 --> 01:45:37,247
Hello, Delores.
How I am today?

1259
01:45:38,248 --> 01:45:40,250
What do you have here?

1260
01:45:44,379 --> 01:45:46,381
What do you have here?

1261
01:45:56,183 --> 01:45:58,185
Oh, no. It's not signed.

1262
01:45:59,853 --> 01:46:01,688
What?

1263
01:46:01,771 --> 01:46:04,566
This is a one-day emergency travel visa.

1264
01:46:04,649 --> 01:46:09,196
To validate authenticity, it needs
to be signed by the supervising officer.

1265
01:46:09,821 --> 01:46:11,823
Dixon?

1266
01:46:11,948 --> 01:46:13,158
Yes.

1267
01:46:13,241 --> 01:46:15,952
Dixon.

1268
01:46:19,456 --> 01:46:23,376
The war in my country is over.

1269
01:46:24,503 --> 01:46:29,424
Yeah. I know. Congratulations.

1270
01:46:29,549 --> 01:46:31,510
It's strange, isn't it, Viktor?

1271
01:46:32,677 --> 01:46:35,055
When you wait so long for one thing?

1272
01:46:36,097 --> 01:46:38,475
One tiny moment.

1273
01:46:38,558 --> 01:46:41,186
I had that moment today, too.

1274
01:46:41,228 --> 01:46:43,522
You see this badge?

1275
01:46:43,563 --> 01:46:47,442
This badge means that I was made
CBP Field Commissioner.

1276
01:46:47,526 --> 01:46:52,531
It means that my authority over the
security of this airport is absolute.

1277
01:46:53,907 --> 01:46:56,326
Your ticket and your passport.

1278
01:46:58,912 --> 01:47:01,331
It's time for you to go home.

1279
01:47:05,252 --> 01:47:08,922
Officer Waylin, please show
Mr. Navorski into the terminal

1280
01:47:09,005 --> 01:47:11,925
and make sure
he does not miss his flight.

1281
01:47:12,008 --> 01:47:14,010
Goodbye, Viktor, and good luck.

1282
01:47:24,646 --> 01:47:26,648
I think I want go New York City.

1283
01:47:29,109 --> 01:47:31,236
Don't make this difficult, Viktor.

1284
01:47:31,319 --> 01:47:34,281
I no more "unacceptable".

1285
01:47:34,322 --> 01:47:37,784
- I told you this is over.
- I go New York.

1286
01:47:40,495 --> 01:47:42,497
Are you sure you want to do that?

1287
01:47:44,332 --> 01:47:46,334
I go New York City now.

1288
01:47:51,298 --> 01:47:56,761
Part of my job is to get rid of
undesirables, and there are quite a few.

1289
01:47:57,971 --> 01:48:00,473
Like this guy, Joe Mulroy.
I think you know him.

1290
01:48:00,557 --> 01:48:04,728
He's been here for 20 years, but he's
been running an after-hour poker game.

1291
01:48:04,853 --> 01:48:06,855
Bringing in liquor and marijuana.

1292
01:48:06,980 --> 01:48:10,984
Poor guy's going to lose his pension.
And I think he has kids, too.

1293
01:48:11,109 --> 01:48:12,152
Yep.

1294
01:48:12,277 --> 01:48:17,157
And then there's this guy, Enrique Cruz.
I think you also know Enrique.

1295
01:48:17,240 --> 01:48:22,245
Enrique has been letting people
into the food preparation area.

1296
01:48:22,329 --> 01:48:24,289
That's a major security breach.

1297
01:48:24,372 --> 01:48:26,500
The poor guy, I think he's a newlywed.

1298
01:48:26,541 --> 01:48:28,668
But I'm going to have to let him go.

1299
01:48:28,710 --> 01:48:33,423
And then there's Gupta Rajan.
He's a janitor.

1300
01:48:33,507 --> 01:48:37,969
But he's wanted for assaulting
a police officer back in India in 1 979.

1301
01:48:39,554 --> 01:48:41,681
I'll have to deport him.

1302
01:48:41,765 --> 01:48:43,725
I will go home.

1303
01:48:44,726 --> 01:48:48,396
- I'm sorry. What did you say?
- I will go home.

1304
01:48:48,480 --> 01:48:50,482
Leave them alone. I will go.

1305
01:48:51,274 --> 01:48:52,943
- Today.
- Yes.

1306
01:48:53,026 --> 01:48:56,071
If you don't get on that plane,
they're all gone.

1307
01:48:56,154 --> 01:48:57,989
- Do you understand?
- Yes.

1308
01:48:58,073 --> 01:48:59,699
OK. Good.

1309
01:49:01,368 --> 01:49:03,078
Your attention please.

1310
01:49:03,161 --> 01:49:09,084
Immediate boarding, gate B-20, for
flight number 309 Air Canada to Ottawa.

1311
01:49:13,588 --> 01:49:14,923
I don't believe you.

1312
01:49:15,006 --> 01:49:18,677
- Viktor, you don't have to do this.
- You can fight these guys.

1313
01:49:18,760 --> 01:49:21,680
- We'll help you.
- Viktor, come on. I owe you so much.

1314
01:49:21,763 --> 01:49:24,766
- Please let me help you.
- This is your friend talking.

1315
01:49:24,850 --> 01:49:27,894
We're all your friends.
We're your family now.

1316
01:49:32,482 --> 01:49:33,483
Gupta.

1317
01:49:33,567 --> 01:49:35,151
Goodbye.

1318
01:49:35,235 --> 01:49:38,155
You try to fool us.

1319
01:49:38,238 --> 01:49:42,868
You make us to think you would walk out,
that you will fight with them.

1320
01:49:42,951 --> 01:49:44,619
Why don't you fight?

1321
01:49:44,744 --> 01:49:49,457
- The war is over.
- Then go. Get lost.

1322
01:49:49,541 --> 01:49:54,087
Get lost. Go home
and tell them you never made it.

1323
01:49:54,171 --> 01:49:58,216
You come this close to America,

1324
01:49:58,300 --> 01:50:02,512
but you don't have the courage
to go from here to here.

1325
01:50:03,972 --> 01:50:05,807
You are a coward.

1326
01:50:05,849 --> 01:50:08,643
The plane is on time.

1327
01:50:08,727 --> 01:50:11,021
You are a coward.

1328
01:50:11,646 --> 01:50:14,191
You are a coward!

1329
01:50:14,274 --> 01:50:15,942
You make me sick!

1330
01:50:15,984 --> 01:50:19,404
What's wrong with you, man?
Settle down.

1331
01:50:19,488 --> 01:50:23,450
Got people looking all around,
looking at me like I'm...

1332
01:50:25,744 --> 01:50:27,204
Look at me.

1333
01:50:28,038 --> 01:50:30,040
Come on, look at me.

1334
01:50:34,669 --> 01:50:36,922
There's something you should know.

1335
01:50:40,926 --> 01:50:44,012
Ladies and gentlemen,
United Airlines Flight 865

1336
01:50:44,054 --> 01:50:47,599
from Krakozhia has landed
and is now taxiing to the gate.

1337
01:50:47,682 --> 01:50:51,394
For those passengers holding tickets
for Flight 866 to Krakozhia,

1338
01:50:51,520 --> 01:50:53,980
we expect departure
to be on schedule.

1339
01:51:09,871 --> 01:51:11,873
Get back, please.

1340
01:51:21,758 --> 01:51:22,968
Gupta.

1341
01:51:35,272 --> 01:51:37,232
Gupta!

1342
01:52:09,097 --> 01:52:11,099
I am going home.

1343
01:52:15,604 --> 01:52:17,606
Get lost.

1344
01:52:28,658 --> 01:52:30,619
Your attention, please.

1345
01:52:30,702 --> 01:52:35,790
Flight 866 to Krakozhia
will be delayed until further notice.

1346
01:52:44,299 --> 01:52:46,968
Do you have an appointment?

1347
01:52:49,262 --> 01:52:52,098
Somebody tell me
what the hell is going on down there!

1348
01:52:55,060 --> 01:52:57,062
We're right behind you.

1349
01:53:01,316 --> 01:53:02,692
Viktor's leaving.

1350
01:53:17,707 --> 01:53:21,169
- Monica, Viktor's leaving.
- I know. He's going home.

1351
01:53:21,253 --> 01:53:23,755
He's going for the front door,
out to the city.

1352
01:53:23,839 --> 01:53:25,340
What?

1353
01:53:34,891 --> 01:53:36,935
Viktor. Remember us.

1354
01:53:37,018 --> 01:53:39,688
From the Discovery Store,
I want to give you this.

1355
01:53:39,771 --> 01:53:40,897
It's good luck.

1356
01:53:41,022 --> 01:53:42,983
A digital camera for cousin Katia.

1357
01:53:43,108 --> 01:53:46,820
I don't know where you're going,
but these will keep your feet warm.

1358
01:53:55,996 --> 01:53:58,498
- Everybody in position?
- We're here.

1359
01:53:58,582 --> 01:54:00,041
Secure the door.

1360
01:54:12,220 --> 01:54:14,181
Sorry, Viktor.

1361
01:54:17,642 --> 01:54:18,768
Take him, Judge.

1362
01:54:20,145 --> 01:54:23,523
Hold it, Viktor. Take it easy.

1363
01:54:25,150 --> 01:54:27,319
You see those doors?

1364
01:54:27,402 --> 01:54:29,946
Those are the entry doors
to New York City.

1365
01:54:30,030 --> 01:54:33,533
To the United States of America.
Turn around.

1366
01:54:43,335 --> 01:54:46,838
It's snowing in the city
and you're going to need that.

1367
01:54:50,884 --> 01:54:51,843
Good luck.

1368
01:54:52,802 --> 01:54:55,805
Oh, no. Oh, no. Oh, no. Oh, no.

1369
01:54:55,847 --> 01:54:57,474
Oh, no. Oh, no. No, no.

1370
01:54:57,557 --> 01:54:58,850
I'm going to miss you.

1371
01:54:58,934 --> 01:55:01,269
Try not to get stuck
wherever you're going.

1372
01:55:01,353 --> 01:55:03,313
Arrest him! Arrest him!

1373
01:55:03,355 --> 01:55:06,274
Goddammit!

1374
01:55:50,986 --> 01:55:52,654
Taxi!

1375
01:56:05,500 --> 01:56:06,835
Thank you.

1376
01:56:46,791 --> 01:56:49,211
Where you go?

1377
01:56:49,294 --> 01:56:54,382
1 61 Lexington. Please take Van Wyck
Expressway to Queensboro Bridge.

1378
01:56:54,466 --> 01:56:56,009
It's faster than BQE.

1379
01:56:56,092 --> 01:56:59,429
- Where you from?
- Krakozhia. Viktor Navorski.

1380
01:56:59,513 --> 01:57:01,806
I'm Goran. Albania.

1381
01:57:01,890 --> 01:57:06,186
- When do you come to New York?
- Thursday.

1382
01:57:15,487 --> 01:57:20,617
You want us to block the south exit
and have AP sweep every vehicle?

1383
01:57:21,618 --> 01:57:23,620
Sir?

1384
01:57:27,874 --> 01:57:30,001
5.30 from Tokyo just landed.

1385
01:57:30,085 --> 01:57:34,214
Got two planes on the tarmac.
Barcelona on approach.

1386
01:57:34,339 --> 01:57:37,759
The night is young
and 1 500 people are headed our way.

1387
01:57:40,095 --> 01:57:43,390
Everybody inside.
Everybody inside.

1388
01:57:43,431 --> 01:57:44,891
Come on, let's go.

1389
01:57:44,975 --> 01:57:46,393
Let's go.

1390
01:58:15,964 --> 01:58:20,594
- Are you checking in, sir?
- No, no. I don't check in.

1391
01:58:20,677 --> 01:58:22,512
I want to go to this place, please.

1392
01:58:22,596 --> 01:58:24,764
The lobby lounge
is around the corner.

1393
01:58:24,806 --> 01:58:28,894
They have happy hour specials
and live music. Do you like jazz?

1394
01:58:28,977 --> 01:58:30,937
The monitor's off.

1395
01:58:35,984 --> 01:58:40,280
The piano's OK. A little more
bass. More bass from the monitor.

1396
01:58:44,284 --> 01:58:48,163
Let's do Killer Joe.
It worked all right last night.

1397
01:58:48,205 --> 01:58:51,166
- Yes?
- You are Benny Golson?

1398
01:58:51,249 --> 01:58:53,627
Yeah. Yes, I am.

1399
01:58:54,878 --> 01:58:59,090
Benny Golson, I am Viktor Navorski.
I am from Krakozhia.

1400
01:58:59,174 --> 01:59:04,763
My father, Dimitar Asenov Navorski,
was great, great fan of your music.

1401
01:59:04,846 --> 01:59:08,350
A jazz fan. Fantastic.

1402
01:59:08,433 --> 01:59:11,770
Would you sign your name, please?

1403
01:59:11,853 --> 01:59:15,941
Can I do it a little later?
We have to get started now.

1404
01:59:16,024 --> 01:59:17,859
- Just a minute.
- I will wait.

1405
01:59:17,901 --> 01:59:19,861
OK.

1406
02:00:24,551 --> 02:00:26,511
Taxi! Taxi!

1407
02:00:48,992 --> 02:00:51,369
Where you want to go?

1408
02:00:54,122 --> 02:00:56,082
I am going home.

